== 安全與地緣政治 ==
[[File:Arctic_Sea_and_Seabed_Claims.jpg|链接=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Arctic_Sea_and_Seabed_Claims.jpg]]
1996年北極理事會成立之際，《渥太華宣言》中有一項腳註表明“北極理事會不應涉及軍事安全領域”。<ref>{{cite web|title=Declaration on the Establishment of the Arctic Council (Ottawa, Canada, 1996)|url=https://www.international.gc.ca/world-monde/international_relations-relations_internationales/arctic-arctique/declaration_ac-declaration_ca.aspx?lang=eng|access-date=September 17, 2021|date=May 10, 2017|archive-date=2022-04-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220404203553/https://www.international.gc.ca/world-monde/international_relations-relations_internationales/arctic-arctique/declaration_ac-declaration_ca.aspx?lang=eng}}</ref>但在2019年，[[美国国务卿|美國國務卿]][[邁克·蓬佩奧|邁克·蓬佩奧]]指出，當前的形勢已經不同以往，北極地區成爲各方力量角力的舞臺，理事會需要適應該未來趨勢。<ref name="clingendael20202">{{Cite report|title=Presence before power: why China became a near-Arctic state|last1=Dams|first1=Ties|last2=van Schaik|first2=Louise|date=2020|publisher=Clingendael Institute|pages=6–19|jstor=resrep24677.5|last3=Stoetman|first3=Adája|jstor-access=free}}</ref>

但總體而言，北極地區的領土爭端通常相當有限。最突出的例子有圍繞[[漢斯島|漢斯島]]（丹麥和加拿大之間）和[[波弗特海|波弗特海]]（美國和加拿大之間）的爭端。<ref name="CIAfactIssues">{{cite web|title=Transnational Issues CIA World Fact Book|url=https://www.cia.gov/the-world-factbook/countries/united-states/|access-date=2012-01-10|publisher=CIA|archive-date=2021-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210321202516/https://www.cia.gov/the-world-factbook/countries/united-states/}}</ref><ref name="InstituteNorth">{{cite web|title=Sea Changes|url=http://www.institutenorth.org/servlet/download?id=35|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070613215643/http://www.institutenorth.org/servlet/download?id=35|archive-date=June 13, 2007}}</ref> 

該地區的領土紛爭，大多數是想爭奪[[北冰洋|北冰洋]]下[[海床|海床]]的專有權。由於[[氣候變遷|氣候變化]]及北冰洋浮冰及凍土加速融化，很多之前無法開採的能源和無法使用的航道如今紛紛變得有利可圖。根據《[[聯合國海洋法公約|聯合國海洋法公約]]》，各國可將從[[领海基线|測算領海寬度的基線]]量起，不應超過二百[[海里|海里]]（370.4公里）內的水體宣示爲[[专属经济区|專屬經濟區]]，並對該範圍內的自然資源擁有專有權，但加拿大、俄羅斯以及丹麥（格陵蘭島）三國卻對'''聯合國大陸架界限委員會'''（UN Commission on the Limits of the Continental Shelf）提交了互相重疊的權力宣稱範圍。一旦大陸架界限委員會作出裁決，三國需開啓談判以分割重疊宣稱的範圍。<ref>{{cite web|title=An Off-the-Shelf Guide to Extended Continental Shelves and the Arctic|url=https://www.lawfareblog.com/shelf-guide-extended-continental-shelves-and-arctic|access-date=2021-08-07|website=Lawfare|last1=Overfield|first1=Cornell|archive-date=2022-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220321073523/https://www.lawfareblog.com/shelf-guide-extended-continental-shelves-and-arctic}}</ref>

亦有部分領土紛爭圍繞在[[西北水道|西北水道]]和[[北方海路|北方海路]]上。

* 加拿大將整條西北水道納爲自己的內海範圍內，意味着加拿大能夠自由控制水道上通行的船隻。而美國則認爲，西北水道是國際水道，任何船隻在任何時候都有權通行，且加方不得關閉水道。加拿大公衆對西北水道的主權問題亦相當關注，且根據民意調查，半數加國公民希望政府能夠嘗試去維護本國對水道的主權，而對比之下，美國則僅有10%的居民對政府有類似要求。<ref name="theglobeandmail1">{{cite news|author=Jill Mahoney|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/politics/canadians-rank-arctic-sovereignty-as-top-foreign-policy-priority/article563348/|title=Canadians rank Arctic sovereignty as top foreign-policy priority|newspaper=The Globe and Mail|access-date=2013-09-24|archive-date=2022-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220321073504/https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/politics/canadians-rank-arctic-sovereignty-as-top-foreign-policy-priority/article563348/}}</ref>
* 以北方海路的爭端則不一樣。俄羅斯僅將海路上一些海峽附近的領域納爲自身的內海範圍，但俄羅斯同時亦要求各商業船隻需先得俄方批准，方可進入俄羅斯的專屬經濟區。

隨着理事會逐漸接納更多的觀察員，後者亦開始表達對北極地區的興趣。中國已經公開表示希望能夠開採格陵蘭島的自然資源。<ref name="economist1">{{cite news|url=https://www.economist.com/news/international/21571127-will-asian-countries-consolidate-or-disrupt-arctic-stability-roar-ice-cracking|title=Outsiders in the Arctic: The roar of ice cracking|newspaper=The Economist|date=2013-02-02|access-date=2013-09-24|archive-date=2019-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191104064725/https://www.economist.com/news/international/21571127-will-asian-countries-consolidate-or-disrupt-arctic-stability-roar-ice-cracking}}</ref>

在軍事方面上，加拿大、丹麥、挪威和俄羅斯都紛紛加強北極地區內的軍事基礎設施建設。<ref name="americansecurityproject1">{{cite web|title=The Arctic: Five Critical Security Challenges | ASPAmerican Security Project|url=http://americansecurityproject.org/featured-items/2013/the-arctic-five-critical-security-challenges/|access-date=2013-09-24|publisher=Americansecurityproject.org|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927012708/http://americansecurityproject.org/featured-items/2013/the-arctic-five-critical-security-challenges/|archive-date=2013-09-27|url-status=dead}}</ref>

雖然各成員國間稍有衝突，但仍有人表示樂觀，認爲理事會可以加強地區穩定。<ref name="Buixade Farre 2014" />挪威海軍上將{{Link-en|哈康·布鲁恩·汉森|Haakon Bruun-Hanssen}}就曾指出，“北極地區可能是全世界最穩定的地區”。北極地區亦有健全的立法和有效的執法。<ref name="economist12">{{cite news|url=https://www.economist.com/news/international/21571127-will-asian-countries-consolidate-or-disrupt-arctic-stability-roar-ice-cracking|title=Outsiders in the Arctic: The roar of ice cracking|newspaper=The Economist|date=2013-02-02|access-date=2013-09-24|archive-date=2019-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191104064725/https://www.economist.com/news/international/21571127-will-asian-countries-consolidate-or-disrupt-arctic-stability-roar-ice-cracking}}</ref>各成員一致達成共識，只有建立良好合作關係，共同承擔對北極地區的研究、航道開發等任務，才能夠惠澤所有相關方。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.economist.com/node/21551029|title=Arctic politics: Cosy amid the thaw|newspaper=The Economist|date=2012-03-24|access-date=2013-09-24|archive-date=2015-04-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403060813/http://www.economist.com/node/21551029}}</ref>

近年來，亦有部分評論稱北極理事會需要開始涉足地區安全和和平方面的事務。2010年的一份問卷調查顯示，大部分挪威、加拿大、芬蘭、冰島和丹麥的受訪者希望將北極納爲[[無核武地帶|無核武地帶]]。<ref>[https://munkschool.utoronto.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/ArcticCouncil_GordonFoundation_2011.pdf Rethinking theTop of the World: Arctic Security Public Opinion Survey] {{Wayback|url=https://munkschool.utoronto.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/ArcticCouncil_GordonFoundation_2011.pdf |date=20220408191239 }}, EKOS, January 2011</ref>而俄羅斯的受訪者則只有少部分有類似訴求，但當中依然有80%的受訪者表示理事會需要開始領導地區的和平建設。<ref>{{cite news|author=Janice Gross Stein And Thomas S. Axworthy|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/opinion/the-arctic-council-is-the-best-way-for-canada-to-resolve-its-territorial-disputes/article574575/|title=The Arctic Council is the best way for Canada to resolve its territorial disputes|newspaper=The Globe and Mail|access-date=2013-09-24|archive-date=2022-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220321073520/https://www.theglobeandmail.com/opinion/the-arctic-council-is-the-best-way-for-canada-to-resolve-its-territorial-disputes/article574575/}}</ref>但直至2014年6月，理事會依然繼續迴避軍事安全方面的議題。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Stability and Peace in the Arctic Ocean through Science Diplomacy|url=http://www.sciencediplomacy.org/perspective/2014/stability-and-peace-in-arctic-ocean-through-science-diplomacy|first1=Paul|date=2014-06-23|journal=Science & Diplomacy|issue=2|volume=3|last1=Berkman|access-date=2022-01-01|archive-date=2022-04-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220426152211/https://www.sciencediplomacy.org/perspective/2014/stability-and-peace-in-arctic-ocean-through-science-diplomacy}}</ref>

